[[File:Control valves.jpg|thumb|Modulating control valves each with 4-20mA I to P converter linked to pneumatic a valve positioner controlling a diaphragm actuator]] An '''air-operated valve''' is a type of power operated [[valve]] that uses air pressure against a [[piston]] or [[diaphragm (mechanics)|diaphragm]] to produce linear or circular movement to operate a valve. Types are 2-way, 3-way and 4-way. The 2 way air-operated valves can be either normally closed or normally opened.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.controlandpower.com/catalog/PDFs/ASCO/ASCO%2035-9%20Engineering%20Information.pdf|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150225122854/http://www.controlandpower.com/catalog/PDFs/ASCO/ASCO%2035-9%20Engineering%20Information.pdf|archive-date=25 February 2015|title=Engineering information, Air valves|pages=455&ndash;456}}</ref>
